							it has not been homogenised or damaged by intense heat. It remains a live food, unharmed and therefore
							retaining its therapeutic properties.</i></p>
			<p style="margin-right:100px"><i><b>3</b> Cosmetics and ointments are prepared by using a lush blend of fresh herbs and
							the finest honeybee ingredients. Many of our most popular products are created from secret Edwardian recipes.</i></p>
			<p style="margin-right:100px">Our products are hand-made from start to finish. We keep it simple, pure and fresh. We bring you
							quality food as nature intended, with minimal human intervention.</p>
			<p><img src="images/ourprep3.jpg" border="0"></p>
			<p style="margin-right:100px">Honey is very similar to fine wines. Honey comes in many colours, flavours and can improve with age.
							There are as many different honeys as there are flower species. Their tastes and textures are bountiful.</p>
			<p style="margin-right:100px">As a bee farmer I look after all my own beehives at several apiary sites around the country. I take a trailer load
							of beehives to specific floral areas which I know will yield a certain type of honey. In this way I am able
							to offer a wide variety of limited single-floral honeys for example Sweet Chestnut, Heather, Linden Blossom, Hawthorn etc.</p>
